The menu of a fat-addicted child: it does not eat breakfast and eats sausage for the evening
More than a third of children from 9 to 13 have overweight problems, with 9% of all pupils and 5% of all children overweight.
Current surveys have shown - obese children usually come from families with unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows once again how important for the healthy development of a human being is the milieu in which he grows up and are the examples that surround him.
There are up to half more sausages on the table on the tables of adipous children than in families where normal-weight children live.
More than 19 percent of the overweight children had fries for dinner on the day before the reconnaissance action under the motto "obesity is not a coincidence."
In families with thickets, sport is not exactly one of the favorite jobs, but the majority of today's students - only 15 percent replied that their parents find their time for active movement at least once a week.
Survey among 900 children
The survey took place last year at the end of the school year, with almost 900 children from primary schools being interviewed throughout the Czech Republic.
This was already the second year of the action "Obesity is not a coincidence," supported by the General Health Fund and the Unilever Society.
To date, more than 12 thousand students from the 4th and 8th classes have participated in the project.
Unhealthy food and a lack of movement in the family are crucial factors that are responsible for the frightening increase in the number of children with overweight or even obesity.
"Only half of the children interviewed led, for example, five times a day, in the mode of eating breakfast-second breakfast-lunch-vesper-dinner - one of the main conditions for a healthy diet," one of the survey results is.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that relative little things, such as the regular breakfast time of the family, are also important for the healthy development of a child.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 percent of the students' families have breakfast.
And - in most families, everyone has breakfast for themselves.
The worst thing was the statement that is not breakfast at all in every tenth family.
Breakfast is considered the foundation of the healthy daily diet.
The survey test showed, among other things, that the families of overweight children often use unhealthy fries.
And almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonades every day (70 percent)
Although more than 40 percent of the children interviewed are sports, only less than half of their parents do so - only 15 percent.
Set up your own menu
Another part of the survey enabled selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own menu from offered opportunities for appetite and opinion.
"What Czech children between 12 and 15 prefer in terms of nutrition is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among their favorite spas were many flour dishes, meat dishes and of course sweet dishes.
"Alarming is above all the great popularity of sweet lemonades," is stressed in the final report on this survey.
At lunch, that is, the main dish, pasta was just in front of poultry.
The children almost didn't like legumes and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunch was very low.
Return to health
At the same time, however, the survey also showed that the children are quite willing to change their eating habits if they get the right information.
"In many cases, the control group of the respondents who completed the questionnaire at the end of the" obesity is not a coincidence, "has seen a significant shift in preferences to healthy nutrition principles," is mentioned in the results of the project.
At the moment, for example, this was the case with the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
The children also crossed poultry or fish much more often in the questionnaire as the main dish of the day and were ready to eat less dumplings or sweet food.
