However, the building was not suitable for space and technical use as a museum - no walls for the hanging of art, no good climate.
However, it was used until contemporary art in Vienna got a new house.
Since 2001 the building was empty and came down more and more.
Now the architect Adolf Krischanitz has redesigned the pavilion, it is now called the "21st House" and will be used as a museum for contemporary art in the future.
