MSS announces a research protocol for finding the gene for obesity
She is the head of a research project to find the gene for obesity in children and young people, supported by IPN specialists.
The Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social - IMSS (Mexico Social Insurance Institute) announced that it is conducting a research project to discover the gene for obesity in children and adolescents under the title "Genetics of obesity in childhood and youth," with which the genetic markers are to be found in conjunction with overweight.
Miguel Cruz López, head of the Unidad de Investigación Médica en Bioquímica (Department of Medical Research, Focus on Biochemistry) at the Hospital de Especialidades del Centro Médico Nacional Siglo XXI, said that an interdisciplinary team, consisting of doctors, nurses, food specialists and social workers, was established.
This team is supported by specialists and students from the post-graduate programme at the Instituto Nacional de Salud Pública (INSP) and the Centro de Investigación y de Estudios Avanzados (Cinveststav) del Instituto Politécnico Nacional (IPN).
The population is invited to participate in the study. Interested parties can come to the sports areas of the IMSS in the Valley of Mexico, where tests with children and young people are carried out every Saturday from 8: 00.
He stressed that the investigation began on the sports field of Cuauhtémoc (in the west of the state of México) and was continued on the sports field of Nezahualcóyolt (in the east of the state of México) since 8 October.
When the target of 500 to 600 research staff is reached, the study will be continued at the sports field of Independencia (in the south of the capital district) and completed at the one of Morelos (in the north of the capital district).
